"I see two things happening," said Mike Zigmont, head of research and trading at Harvest Volatility Management in New York.  In his prepared remarks, Powell stopped short of providing a clearer picture regarding the timing of the central bank's tapering of asset purchases or hiking interest rates, the key elements of its dovish monetary policy aimed at helping the economy recover from the pandemic recession.
